# demoApp
demoApp mobile app using Expo CLI setup for React Native.

Setup React Native Environment For IOS

Option 1:  React native CLI 
1. Install npm and node.js
Go to the node.js website. Download and install node.js
https://nodejs.org/en/

2. Install Homebrew
Go to the Homebrew  https://brew.sh/
Open your terminal and run the following code to install
/usr/bin/ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"

3. Install Watchman
Run the following code to install Watchman.
brew install watchman

4. Install RN CLI
Now, run the following code to install React Native.
sudo npm install -g react-native-cli
5. Android — Install Android Studio
https://developer.android.com/studio/install.html
6. IOS — Install XCode
For IOS development you will need XCode
7. 
Create First App
cd Desktop
react-native init reactTutorialApp
----

Option 2: Expo CLI
1. Install Expo CLI
npm install -g expo-cli
2. Create First App
expo init AwesomeProject
3. run 
cd AwesomeProject
npm start # you can also use: expo start
